[thinking] **Exploring ReflectionConverter API**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m considering the ReflectionConverter's public API and how it marshals/unmarshals data if it’s registered in XStream. I need to think about the required constructors. XStream seems to have the ability to register converters with priorities, which is interesting. Also, I notice the AnnotationReflectionConverter needs both a Mapper and a ReflectionProvider. I guess it might be worth checking out xstream.getMapper() and maybe exploring getReflectionProvider as well. Let's dig into the public methods!
